## 3) UI I18N Implementation (Web App)

### 3.1 Use an i18n library consistently
Pick one and enforce:
- **React:** `react-intl` OR `i18next` (with ICU support preferred)
- Store keys in `/packages/i18n/locales/{locale}.json`

### 3.2 Key naming standard
- `screen.section.component.label`
Examples:
- `nav.dashboard`
- `mission.checkpoint.submit`
- `errors.permissionDenied`
- `ai.safety.blocked.title`

### 3.3 Prohibited patterns (CI must catch)
- Hardcoded strings in components
- String concatenation that breaks translation
- Inline locale-specific logic in UI components

Allowed:
- Debug/test labels in dev-only code paths, flagged and excluded in prod builds.

### 3.4 Build-time checks (must implement)
- Script to scan for hardcoded strings (best-effort) and enforce:
  - No literal text in JSX except approved whitelist
  - No `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` for translatable content
- Enforce locale files exist and parse.

**VIBE gate:** `i18n:lint` must pass.

