## 5) API & Data Layer Locale Awareness

### 5.1 Locale propagation
Every request to `scholesa-api` must include:
- `Accept-Language` header OR
- `X-Scholesa-Locale`

Server must:
- resolve locale (prefer user profile setting)
- log locale on request context
- propagate locale to `scholesa-ai` calls

### 5.2 Firestore data fields
For any localized content stored:
- store as either:
  - single source key + runtime translation (preferred), OR
  - `localizedText: { en: "...", "zh-CN": "...", "zh-TW": "...", th: "..." }`

Avoid mixing strategies within the same feature.

